name: formation of ATP
reaction: 10 Carbon + 8 H2(g) + 2.5 N2(g) + 6.5 O2(g) + 3 Phosphorus <=> ATP

name: formation of ADP
reaction: 10 Carbon + 7.5 H2(g) + 2.5 N2(g) + 5 O2(g) + 2 Phosphorus <=> ADP

name: formation of AMP
reaction: 10 Carbon + 7 H2(g) + 2.5 N2(g) + 3.5 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> AMP

name: formation of L-Cysteine
reaction: Sulfur + 3 Carbon + 3.5 H2(g) + 0.5 N2(g) + O2(g) <=> L-Cysteine

name: formation of Glycerone phosphate
reaction: 3 Carbon + 3.5 H2(g) + 3 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> Glycerone phosphate

name: formation of Adenylyl sulfate
reaction: Sulfur + 10 Carbon + 7 H2(g) + 2.5 N2(g) + 5 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> Adenylyl sulfate

name: formation of Acetyl phosphate
reaction: 2 Carbon + 2.5 H2(g) + 2.5 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> Acetyl phosphate

name: formation of L-Cystine
reaction: 2 Sulfur + 6 Carbon + 6 H2(g) + N2(g) + 2 O2(g) <=> L-Cystine

name: formation of 3',5'-Cyclic AMP
reaction: 10 Carbon + 6 H2(g) + 2.5 N2(g) + 3 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> 3',5'-Cyclic AMP

name: formation of O-Phospho-L-serine
reaction: 3 Carbon + 4 H2(g) + 0.5 N2(g) + 3 O2(g) + Phosphorus <=> O-Phospho-L-serine
